    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) and **Kyle Tucker** (81.94), who represent our strongest plays. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a premium leadoff spot and favorable wind conditions against Wacha, while **Kyle Tucker**\u2014despite a pending lineup status\u2014remains a core asset due to his elite xwOBA and a generous wind-aided boost at his park. **Jackson Merrill** also presents significant upside with a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against Sugano, making him an essential start. We are particularly aggressive with our exposure to the Fuentes matchup; **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Brady House** (63.19) are primary beneficiaries of the soft SP_xERA of 5.07, allowing both to clear the 60-point threshold comfortably.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's roster was keeping **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (58.68) on the bench. He fell just short of **Marcell Ozuna** (59.52) for the UTIL slot, primarily due to a projected platoon disadvantage that suppressed his base efficiency. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** displays a superior xwOBA of 0.384, the optimizer favored the overall lineup construction and the slightly higher volume expectations for **Marcell Ozuna** in the #4 hole. Elsewhere, we are monitoring **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** closely as their scores are contingent on assumed batting orders; should their actual placements fall significantly lower than the projected #2 and #5 spots, their efficiency scores will adjust downward accordingly. **Liam Hicks** remains a marginal start today at 44.89, serving as a placeholder for the catcher slot; he is the only rostered player currently hovering near our \"below floor\" threshold, though his platoon advantage keeps him marginally ahead of the bench options.",
